Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery ribbed vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section and contains many small white inclusions, the interior is spotted with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a brown slip and faint traces of a black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393849) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393849)
